title: NationalCityMakersCaravan
name: NationalCityMakersCaravan
description:
The National CityMakers Caravan is a five-month long campaign for homeless citizens in urban India, organised by the Indo Global Social Service Society (IGSSS) in collaboration with its partners and supporters across the country. The campaign seeks to address the issues of urban poverty and inadequate shelters for homeless citizens or ‘CityMakers’, using a rights-based approach.

Most CityMakers are migrants from villages, who moved to cities looking for better livelihoods. However, urban areas offer them only irregular, uncertain employment, in addition to an attendant set of problems such as high cost of living, homelessness and inadequate community support systems. Even basic amenities like water, sanitation, health and education are a distant dream for this section of Indians.
